### Constructor

~~~ .php
// `Elevator($input, $chunk = 5, $index = 0, $path = true, $config = [])`
$elevator = new Elevator([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], 3, 0, 'foo/bar');
$elevator_str = $elevator . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$elevator = [
    'up' => null,
    '0' => 'foo/bar',
    'down' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$elevator_str = '<span>▲</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▼</a>';
~~~

To create horizontal elevator:

~~~ .php
$elevator = new Elevator([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], 3, 0, 'foo/bar', [
    'up' => 'previous',
    'down' => 'next'
], 'your_namespace');

Hook::set('elevator.your_namespace', function($content) {
    return str_replace(['&#x25B2;', '&#x25BC;'], ['&#x25C0;', '&#x25B6;'], $content);
});

$elevator_str = $elevator . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$elevator = [
    'previous' => null,
    '0' => 'foo/bar',
    'next' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$elevator_str = '<span>◀</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▶</a>';
~~~